{
  "texts": [
    "With the advancement of current technology, screening large libraries of fragments has become more feasible, resulting in higher hit rates.",
    "These fragments can subsequently be extended, merged, skipped, or linked to construct novel molecules.",
    "In traditional FBDD practices, a majority of researchers opt to utilize existing fragment libraries for molecular fragmentation.",
    "Fragmentation through libraries is a prevalent chemical computation approach commonly employed in computer-aided drug design and molecular simulation research 7.",
    "However, fragmentbased fragmentation is a heuristic method that might not encompass all potential molecular fragments."
  ]
}